tage with\nsize and corresponding reduction of energy. Interconnect resistance is a\ncritical obstacle for scaling beyond 10 nm dimensions. We project a less\ndetrimental impact of interconnect resistance and show that MESO logic is\namenable for highly resistive interconnects (100 uOhm.cm-1 mOhm.cm) which opens\na possibility to use nano-metallic (width < bulk electron mean free path) or\ndoped semiconducting wires (width<5 nm). A scalable, CMOS compatible,\nnon-volatile logic family proposed here may enable the next multi-generational\nscaling of computing devices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Dec 2015 01:13:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 5 Mar 2017 05:05:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-07"}
